'''Damer''' is a [[Impact crater|crater]] on [[Mercury (planet)|Mercury]] at latitude 36.36 N, longitude 115.81 W and is inside the [[Shakespeare quadrangle]]. It is 60&nbsp;km wide and was named after the English sculptor [[Anne Seymour Damer]], and the name was approved on June 18, 2013 by the IAU.<ref>{{cite web|work=Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature (USGS)|title=Damer|url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/15139|publisher=[[International Astronomical Union]]|accessdate=November 30, 2017}}</ref>

Damer is located east of the ray crater [[Degas (crater)|Degas]] and west of [[Gibran (crater)|Gibran]], NNE is the [[Whitman (crater)|crater Whitman]]. Rays from the [[Degas (crater)|Degas]] protrude into the northernmost rim and north of the crater. The crater features a circular central peak with a hollow in the middle.

